    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-05-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-05-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="497"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d497">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Minister <persName type="to">Powell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-05-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 11, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 697.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose copy of a letter from Mr. Elie A.
                        Mansour,<note n="a" xml:id="d497fna">Not printed.</note> who alleges that he
                    is an American citizen and that he is suffering damages from the Haitian
                    Government because of their refusal to issue a license to carry on his
                    business.</p>
                <p>You will examine the case and report to the Department.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">F. B. Loomis.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
